<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Fowl" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Fowl,</orth> subst. bird: <bibl n="shak. pht 10" default="NO" valid="yes">Phoen. 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 507" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 507</bibl> (masc.). <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 2, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.92" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 92</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.209" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 209</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.95" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.2.21" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 2, 21</bibl> <emph>(a struck f. or a hurt wild-duck.</emph> Perhaps here and in some other passages the woodcock is meant). <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.6.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 6, 19</bibl>. Plur. <cit><quote>--s:</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1335" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1335</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.79" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 79</bibl>. Plur. <cit><quote>f.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 511" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 511</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tn 4.2.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. IV, 2, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.68" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 3, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.4.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 4, 97</bibl>.
